![](https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5d56e145f80b7500016ba502/e7233704-a14b-499b-a55a-98d0fec55a3f/e262.jpg)

No news this week, but we still have TONS to cover as we recap and review Avengers: Earth's Mightiest Heroes #1-8 written by Joe Casey with art by Scott Kolins. In this retelling of the formation of one of the most famous superhero teams to date, we discover hidden motives, pathos and in our heroes, as they put aside their differences for the greater good. Don't miss a beat as we watch these five individuals learn to work as a team, and forge a legend!  
   
If you can, please leave us a **_review_** on [**ITunes**](https://podcasts.apple.com/us/podcast/major-issues-podcast/id1321720972) so we can grow our audience and grow as podcasters! Rate us where ever podcasts are found. Don't forget to check out our merchandise! All episodes of Major Issues are brought to you by **ComicBook Clique**, the only stop for the latest and greatest things to come to comic books and comic book media.  
  
